01:00:24.010 --> 01:00:25.562
We're on camera.

01:00:25.562 --> 01:00:27.520
Each of these decay--
each of these transitions

01:00:27.520 --> 01:00:29.140
may also have its own half-life.

01:00:29.140 --> 01:00:31.210
So between isometric
transitions,

01:00:31.210 --> 01:00:34.175
they're usually very, very
fast, but once in a while

01:00:34.175 --> 01:00:34.675
they're not.

01:00:38.790 --> 01:00:42.950
Like technetium-99
metastable to technetium-99

01:00:42.950 --> 01:00:46.340
has a half-life of
around six days,

01:00:46.340 --> 01:00:50.730
which is why it's so useful
as a medical isotope.

01:00:50.730 --> 01:00:53.210
So when you see something
marked M for metastable,

01:00:53.210 --> 01:00:57.560
all that means is there
