01:04:01.780 --> 01:04:04.930
instead of six years later,
it's just kind of nice.

01:04:04.930 --> 01:04:06.590
So that's easy.

01:04:06.590 --> 01:04:08.430
Let's go to the more
challenging one.

01:04:11.390 --> 01:04:13.280
What is the source
of isotope N2?

01:04:16.082 --> 01:04:17.272
AUDIENCE: Decay from N1?

01:04:17.272 --> 01:04:18.480
MICHAEL SHORT: Decay from N1.

01:04:18.480 --> 01:04:21.744
So how would I
mathematically write that?

01:04:21.744 --> 01:04:23.910
AUDIENCE: Just lambda 1 N1.

01:04:23.910 --> 01:04:27.780
MICHAEL SHORT: Just lambda 1 N1.

01:04:27.780 --> 01:04:33.780
And what is the
destruction of isotope N2?

01:04:33.780 --> 01:04:35.679
Anyone else?

01:04:35.679 --> 01:04:36.932
AUDIENCE: Lambda 2 N2?

01:04:36.932 --> 01:04:38.390
MICHAEL SHORT:
Takes the same form.

01:04:38.390 --> 01:04:40.640
It depends on the decay
concept of isotope 2

01:04:40.640 --> 01:04:43.280
and the amount of
isotope 2 that's there.

01:04:47.570 --> 01:04:48.920
How about isotope 3?

01:04:48.920 --> 01:04:50.848
Where does that come from?

01:04:55.186 --> 01:04:56.308
AUDIENCE: Lambda 2 N2?

01:04:56.308 --> 01:04:57.350
MICHAEL SHORT: That's it.

01:04:57.350 --> 01:05:01.310
The source is lambda 2 N2.

01:05:01.310 --> 01:05:03.276
What are the sinks
or the destruction?

01:05:03.276 --> 01:05:04.150
AUDIENCE: Nothing.

01:05:04.150 --> 01:05:05.860
MICHAEL SHORT: Nothing.

01:05:05.860 --> 01:05:10.210
So we have a very simple set
of posed differential equations

01:05:10.210 --> 01:05:13.540
to describe the production and
the destruction of these three

01:05:13.540 --> 01:05:14.830
isotopes.

01:05:14.830 --> 01:05:18.670
So let's imagine now
that N1 was, let's say,

01:05:18.670 --> 01:05:22.490
radium, which exists all
throughout the soil and rocks;

01:05:22.490 --> 01:05:27.040
N2 is radon, the gas that's
produced from radium decay;

01:05:27.040 --> 01:05:30.640
and then N3 could be let's
say one of the stable daughter

01:05:30.640 --> 01:05:31.877
products of radon.

01:05:31.877 --> 01:05:33.460
So these are the
sorts of calculations

01:05:33.460 --> 01:05:35.688
that are done all the
time in real life to see--

01:05:35.688 --> 01:05:37.480
if you know how much
radium is in the rock,

01:05:37.480 --> 01:05:39.850
how much radon do you
expect to breathe in?

01:05:39.850 --> 01:05:42.850
Because at the same time
you're producing radon

01:05:42.850 --> 01:05:44.740
from radium decay.

01:05:44.740 --> 01:05:47.410
And the radon is
decaying itself.

01:05:47.410 --> 01:05:49.750
So you can't just say, oh,
the activity of the radium

01:05:49.750 --> 01:05:51.700
equals the amount of
radon because it's

01:05:51.700 --> 01:05:54.490
being created and destroyed
all at the same time,

01:05:54.490 --> 01:05:56.940
and it depends on how
much there is around.

01:05:56.940 --> 01:05:59.650
Same thing with nuclear
activation analysis.

01:05:59.650 --> 01:06:05.470
